&lt;p&gt;The Territory Sales Manager is tasked with business production for a select group of appointed Agencies and Brokers. This role is fundamental in building a book of business. This role is 100% remote.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive Cowbell’s distribution strategy for the defined territory&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively onboard newly established relationships throughout the territory&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceed production quota through proven distribution management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and implement a sales strategy for a defined geographical territory&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make an immediate impact with currently appointed brokers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Meet and manage weekly, monthly and annual activity metrics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct virtual and in-person meetings, building relationships with account managers up to executive leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with a passionate team, have fun, grow, learn, and teach the company along the way.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a point of accountability for distribution success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Cowbell needs from you:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of commercial insurance experience in a business development or production underwriting role required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years working in the defined territory with established retail and or wholesale relationships (immediate impact expected day one)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cyber, Tech E&amp;amp;O and/or Professional lines insurance experience required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-starter, self-motivated and results-oriented mentality. You take initiative to solve problems with high energy and urgency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven success in distribution with an emphasis on growing new clients (Retail or Wholesale)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Start-up experience a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
